19/12/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- A recent poll suggests overwhelming public support in Albania for the country's EU accession, according to regional media reports at the weekend. The results of the survey, conducted from October to November, found that 83.9 per cent of citizens back the idea of Albania's entry in the EU. Members of the business community were the biggest supporters. 
In other news, Prime Minister Sali Berisha praised the level of bilateral co-operation with neighbouring Greece, in an interview with the Greek news agency ANA on Saturday (17 December). Berisha also said he plans an official visit to Greece soon. (Albanian News, Kathimerini - 19/12/05; Focus, MPA - 18/12/05)
